Use the standard library
This is how to maximum of arr and k:
   Remember that sorted is bubble_sort of arr
   Remember that n is sorted's length
   Remember that start is diff of n and k
   Remember that result is []
   Remember that i is start
   Do this k times:
      Add result to item i in sorted
      Increase i
   End do
   The answer is result
Now you know
>>> maximum of [-3, -4, 5] and 3
[-4, -3, 5]
>>> maximum of [4, -4, 4] and 2
[4, 4]
>>> maximum of [-3, 2, 1, 2, -1, -2, 1] and 1
[2]